# Code of Conduct

## Our Commitment
JavaKids Lite is built to create opportunities for young learners.  
We expect everyone interacting with this project to maintain a respectful, supportive and professional environment.

## Expected Behavior
- Be respectful and constructive.  
- Provide clear and helpful feedback.  
- Support a safe and inclusive space for communication.  
- Use language suitable for a community focused on education and youth empowerment.

## Unacceptable Behavior
- Harassment or discrimination of any kind.  
- Threatening or aggressive language.  
- Sharing harmful, illegal or unsafe content.  
- Any action that puts users or contributors at risk.

## Reporting Concerns
If you see unacceptable behavior, please report it through GitHub Issues.  
All reports will be reviewed by the project maintainer.

## Maintainer Responsibility
The project maintainer may remove comments, issues or contributions that violate this code of conduct in order to protect the project and community.

Thank you for helping make JavaKids Lite a positive environment.
